Eskom has implemented Stage 2 load shedding as from 12:00 today (5 February) until 23:00 on Sunday, 7 February. The load shedding schedule for Louis Trichardt, Levubu, Valdezia, Elim areas, Waterval, Chavani, Vleifontein, Ximausa, Blinkwater and Rotterdam, Mashau, Vuwani areas, Nesengani, Madombidzha areas and Sinthumule areas are as follows: 5 February (no load shedding); 6 February from 09:00 to 11:30 and again from 17:00 to 19:30; and 7 February from 17:00 to 19:30. The load shedding schedule for Musina Town, Nancefield, Leeudraai, Tshipise Forever Resort, Pontdrif, Alldays, Soutpan, Bochum and all Nzhelele Villages are: 5 February from 23:00 to 01:30; 6 February from 07:00 to 09:30; and 7 February from 07:00 to 09:30 and again from 15:00 to 17:30. The load shedding schedule for Tshakhuma, Lwamondo, Shayandima, Muledane, Thohoyandou, Sibasa, Ngovhela, Phiphidi, Gondeni, Vhufuli, Vondwe, Makonde, Tshikweta Thengwe, Sanari, Makuya, Masisi, Malale, Madimbo, Muswodi etc and all Mutale areas are: 5 February from 12:00 to 13:30; 6 February from 11:00 to 13:30 and again from 19:00 to 21:30; and 7 February from 19:00 to 21:30. The load shedding schedule for the Malamulele areas, including Mangondi and Mulenzhe, Hlanganani areas, Masia, Majozi, Tiyani, Mahatlani, Bungeni, Basani, Nwamatatani, Olifantshoek Masakona, Njhakajhaka, Nkuzana, etc and Giyani are: 5 February (no load shedding); 6 February from 07:00 to 09:30 and again from 15:00 to 17:30; and 7 February from 15:00 to 17:30. The load shedding schedule for Mukondeni, Mashamba, Tshivhuyuni, Mulima, Nthabalala, Tshitale, Muwaweni, Mbhokota, Riverplats, Botlokwa and Soekmekaar are: 5 February (no load shedding); 6 February from 05:00 to 07:30 and again from 13:00 to 15:30; and 7 February from 13:00 to 15:30 and again from 21:00 to 23:30.